But we have a closer exception in the Theban legion under Julian, who were willing‚ as Ambrose says, to use their arms for the State, but not against Ohristians; when required to do this, they obeyed the King of heaven, not the emperor of earth. So we read that, of the soldiers whose office it was to exe- cute the condemned, those who had been converted died rather than lay their hands on the Christians.
